Guy Langley for ''[[Computer and Video Games]]'' compared the game to ''[[Gauntlet (1985 video game)|Gauntlet]]'', noting that ''Avenger'' was more of an adventure and has "smarter graphics".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://archive.org/details/Computer_Video_Games_Issue_068_1987-06_EMAP_Publishing_GB/page/n31/mode/2up | title=Computer & Video Games - Issue 068 (1987-06)(EMAP Publishing)(GB) | date=June 1987 }}</ref>

Rich Pelley for ''[[Your Sinclair]]'' gave the game a rating of 86 and praised its variety, with elements of maze games, beat-em ups, and puzzlers.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://archive.org/details/your-sinclair-58/page/n49/mode/2up | title=Your Sinclair Magazine Issue 58 | date=October 1990 }}</ref>

''[[Zzap!64|Zzap!]]'' rated the game at 86%, calling it "highly competent".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://archive.org/details/zzapp_64_issue_022_600dpi/page/n29/mode/2up | title=Zzap! 64 Issue 022 (HQ) }}</ref>

Mike Roberts for ''[[Computer Gamer]]'' rated the game at 85% overall and complimented the life energy system.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://archive.org/details/Computer_Gamer_Issue_22_1987-01_Argus_Press_GB/page/n39/mode/2up | title=Computer Gamer - Issue 22 (1987-01)(Argus Press)(GB) | date=January 1987 }}</ref>

''[[Amtix]]'' rated the game at 73% overall, noting that it was too similar to the original ''Way of the Tiger''.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://archive.org/details/amtix-magazine-15/page/n124/mode/2up | title=Amtix Magazine Issue 15 | date=January 1987 }}</ref>

''[[Commodore User]]'' scored the game 7 out of 10 overall, noting its "tough arcade adventure-style".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://archive.org/details/commodore-user-magazine-40/page/n30/mode/2up | title=Commodore User Magazine Issue 40 | date=January 1987 }}</ref>

